    <h2>Operational Metrics</h2>
    
    <h3>API Utilization</h3>
    <p>
      The migration to the new microservices architecture was completed in February, resulting in improved latency and reliability across the board. The 99.9th percentile latency dropped from 120ms to 45ms.
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Total Requests:</strong> 1.4 Billion (up 12% YoY)</li>
      <li><strong>Uptime:</strong> 99.995%</li>
      <li><strong>Peak Requests/Second:</strong> 4,200 (March 15th)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Infrastructure Expansion</h3>
    <p>
      We have successfully provisioned 3 new storage clusters in the primary data center to support the anticipated growth from the document generation service. This adds 5 PB of high-speed NVMe storage to our capacity.
    </p>

    <h2>Outlook for Q2</h2>
    <p>
      Our primary focus for Q2 will be the general availability release of the document generation API, accompanied by a new self-service portal for enterprise clients. We anticipate a 15% increase in compute usage and are scaling our Kubernetes clusters accordingly.
    </p>

